{"id":483296,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joshua_Fishman","text":"Joshua Aaron Fishman (Yiddish: \u05E9\u05D9\u05E7\u05DC \u05E4\u05BF\u05D9\u05E9\u05DE\u05D0\u05B7\u05DF \u2014 Shikl Fishman; July 18, 1926 \u2013 March 1, 2015) was an American linguist. He specialized in the sociology of language, language planning, bilingual education, and language and ethnicity.\nFishman was born in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania. He died in The Bronx, New York, aged 88.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Yiddish","surface_form":"Yiddish","offset":22},{"uri":"Americans","surface_form":"American","offset":100},{"uri":"Linguist","surface_form":"linguist","offset":109},{"uri":"Sociology_of_language","surface_form":"sociology of language","offset":141},{"uri":"Language_planning","surface_form":"language planning","offset":164},{"uri":"Bilingual_education","surface_form":"bilingual education","offset":183},{"uri":"Language","surface_form":"language","offset":208},{"uri":"Ethnicity","surface_form":"ethnicity","offset":221},{"uri":"Philadelphia","surface_form":"Philadelphia","offset":252},{"uri":"Pennsylvania","surface_form":"Pennsylvania","offset":266},{"uri":"The_Bronx","surface_form":"The Bronx","offset":291},{"uri":"New_York","surface_form":"New York","offset":302}]}